Interface MappedRequestAttributesFactory<T extends java.lang.Enum<T> & AzCategoryId>

Type Parameters:
T - 
public interface MappedRequestAttributesFactory<T extends java.lang.Enum<T> & AzCategoryId>

This is primarily an internal interface used to create a MappedRequestAttributes object with a specific AzCategoryId as indicated by the generic parameter .

Method Summary
 MappedRequestAttributes<T> createObject(PepRequest ctx)
          Create an MappedRequestAttributes Object that contains one of the underlying AzEntity attribute collections that are contained in the PepRequest with the AzCategoryId specified by the generic parameter .
 java.util.List<JavaObjectMapper> getMappers()
          Return the List of JavaObjectMappers associated with AzCategoryId of the MappedRequestAttributes Objects of the generic category produced by this factory.
 java.util.Set<java.lang.Class> getSupportedClasses()
          Returns a Set of all the classes that are supported by the Mapper that implements this interface.
 void setMappers(java.util.List<JavaObjectMapper> mappers)
          Set the mappers that will be used by each category: Subject, Action, Resource, Environment.

setMappers

void setMappers(java.util.List<JavaObjectMapper> mappers)
Set the mappers that will be used by each category: Subject, Action, Resource, Environment. The list of mappers for each category defines the objects that may be submitted for that category and how the information in those objects get mapped to xacml AttributeId and AttributeValue.
